A 19-year-old commuter died after she was struck by a rock in the Bellville area while travelling on a train last weekend. CAPE TOWN - Metrorail says it's noted an increase in the number of trains being stoned in Cape Town.A 19-year-old commuter died after she was struck by a rock in the Bellville area while travelling on a train last weekend.The railway operator has since increased security between the Bellville and Kuils River stations.Metrorail's Riana Scott says: It is incredibly difficult to police stoning. We are keeping an eye on it and cases are increasing. Unfortunately, when trains go through informal settlements commuters complain that it s children who throw stones. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)